--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
DESCRIPTION
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

This role manages motd.

The contents of '/etc/motd' are displayed by login after a successful login but
just before it executes the login shell.

For more detailed information on the usage and available configuration options
please consult the following sections.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
USAGE
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

INSTALL
  - hosts: all
    roles:
     - role: motd
       motd_state: 'install'
       motd_env_color: '1;31m'
       motd_env_name: 'Testing'
       motd_host_description: 'Test Host'
       motd_motd_template: 'robomon'
       motd_os_color: '0;37m'

DISABLE
  - hosts: all
    roles:
     - role: motd
       motd_state: 'disable'

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
VARIABLES
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

ROLE
  motd_state
    Specify predetermined 'motd_state' variable (string).
    Notice: 'motd' is a core file and can therefore not be removed.

    Install: 'true' | 'yes' | 'install'
    Disable: 'stop' | 'off' | 'disable'
    Default: 'install'

  motd_env_color
    Specify predetermined 'motd_env_color' variable (string).
    The following colors codes are compatible with Bourne Again Shell (BASH).
    The codes represent both the regular (R) and bold (B) font style.

    Black (R) : '0;30m'
    Black (B) : '1;30m'
    Red (R)   : '0;31m'
    Red (B)   : '1;31m'
    Green (R) : '0;32m'
    Green (B) : '1;32m'
    Yellow (R): '0;33m'
    Yellow (B): '1;33m'
    Blue (R)  : '0;34m'
    Blue (B)  : '1;34m'
    Purple (R): '0;35m'
    Purple (B): '1;35m'
    Cyan (R)  : '0;36m'
    Cyan (B)  : '1;36m'
    White (R) : '0;37m'
    White (B) : '1;37m'
    Default   : '1;31m'

  motd_env_name
    Specify arbitrary 'motd_env_name' variable (string).

    Examples: 'Production' | 'Integration' | 'Testing' | 'Development'
    None    : ''
    Default : 'Production'

  motd_host_description
    Specify arbitrary 'motd_host_description' variable (string).

    Examples: 'Backup Server' | 'Database Server' | 'Mail Server' | 'Web Server'
    None    : ''
    Default : ''

  motd_motd_template
    Specify arbitrary 'motd_motd_template' variable (string).
    Any value other than 'main' requires a Jinja2 file to be created.
    The custom Jinja2 file for an example configuration called 'example' needs
    to be placed as follows: 'motd/templates/example/motd.j2'

    Examples: 'example' | 'environment' | 'hostname'
    Default : 'robomon'

  motd_os_color
    Specify predetermined 'motd_os_color' variable (string). 
    The following colors codes are compatible with Bourne Again Shell (BASH).
    The codes represent both the regular (R) and bold (B) font style.

    Black (R) : '0;30m'
    Black (B) : '1;30m'
    Red (R)   : '0;31m'
    Red (B)   : '1;31m'
    Green (R) : '0;32m'
    Green (B) : '1;32m'
    Yellow (R): '0;33m'
    Yellow (B): '1;33m'
    Blue (R)  : '0;34m'
    Blue (B)  : '1;34m'
    Purple (R): '0;35m'
    Purple (B): '1;35m'
    Cyan (R)  : '0;36m'
    Cyan (B)  : '1;36m'
    White (R) : '0;37m'
    White (B) : '1;37m'
    Default   : '1;31m'

